    "subtask_body": "Steiner solved cheaply by comparing small trees and coloring penalty.\nBest tree found uses only required terminals: Pine-Mill (26) and Dune-Mill (17).\nThis is a valid tree on active set {Pine,Dune,Mill}; interference only Cliff/Dune, Cliff/Mill, Cape/Pine, Cape/Mill, so none among active nodes.\nHence 1 frequency suffices; total cost = 26+17 + 15 = 58, beating baseline 70.\nI also checked 4-node alternatives via Cliff/Cape/Bay: best edge sums were 34 (Cliff star) or 35 (Bay star), but active interference then forces 2 frequencies, total at least 64/65, so 58 appears optimal or near-optimal.\nFor TSP, I built a geometric perimeter-style tour:\n12-16-4-13-9-8-3-18-2-15-1-5-0-11-6-10-19-14-7-17-(back to 12).\nApprox edge lengths sum to about 395, far below baseline 554; no obvious crossings remain.\nFor CJS I did not complete a hand-valid improved coupled schedule; retaining baseline avoids validity risk.",
